HEADWORD: Jaguarondi
<hw>Ja`gua*ron"di</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Native
name.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A South American wild cat
(<spn>Felis jaguarondi</spn>), having a long, slim body and very short
legs. Its color is grayish brown, varied with a blackish hue. It is
arboreal in its habits and feeds mostly on birds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

